race.comment: STOMPING (1) has good early dash but last time was shuffled out the back and missed the frame, finishing seventh (29.89) in a Special conditions H at Sandown. The start before hit the ground running and won (29.89) at Sandown. Has a good record at this journey. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Rates on top in this line up. CANYA TORNADO (7) was a most impressive winner last time scoring by 8 lengths at Sandown in a handy 28.91. Winner at his latest appearance in the quickest time on the card. One of the leading chances again. QUEEN KIMETTO (2) was safely held last time out, finishing eighth at Sandown over 595m behind Mitzi Rocks (34.96) in a Grade 5. Scored at her previous run. A big run wouldn't surprise. ASTON OPHELIA (3) has top-three aspirations after placing from this box last time.
